“I have people that drop things off on the porch because they know that I use the stuff that everybody else throws away,” she said. 

Her husband Ken, who books her shows, said it’s difficult and competitive to get gallery space. “But getting into the libraries, it seems like there’s a lot more receptivity,” he said.

They have become one of their preferred places to show. 

“It’s just kind of nice to see artwork out in a public place like that,” he said. 

